title: For Sale:  Henry BIG BOY Order of The Arrow 44MAG H006OA
postcontent: Big Boy "Order of the Arrow Centennial Edition" In 1915, the Order of the Arrow (OA) was founded and has recognized Scouts and Scouters who best exemplify the Scout Oath and Law in their daily lives. Today, the OA is recognized as Scouting’s National Honor Society expanding its reach beyond camping to include broader service to Scouting and community. To celebrate 100 years of the Order of the Arrow and honor this high mark of distinction, Henry Repeating Arms is proud to introduce the Order of the Arrow Centennial Rifle. This special rifle commemorates The Order of the Arrow’s vision as stated by Co-Founder E. Urner Goodman, “The Order of the Arrow is a ‘thing of the spirit’ rather than of mechanics. Organization, operational procedure, and paraphernalia are necessary in any large and growing movement, but they are not what count in the end. The things of the spirit count: Brotherhood, in a day when there is too much hatred at home and abroad; Cheerfulness, in a day when the pessimists have the floor; Service, in a day when millions are interested only in getting or grasping rather than giving.” This Henry Big Boy .44 Magnum commemorative rifle is made in the USA by American craftsmen. Built upon Henry’s legacy of reliability, accuracy and smooth engineered action, this tribute rifle is like owning a piece of American history. The right side of the brass receiver features a black filled etching of the new Order of the Arrow totem with the banner CENTURIES OF SERVICE to commemorate the 1915 founding. The left side displays a black filled etching with the Boy Scouts of America Fleur-de-Lis emblem and banners with the motto A BROTHERHOOD OF CHEERFUL SERVICE and ORDER OF THE ARROW. The right side of the American Walnut stock is laser etched and hand-painted with the Order of the Arrow Centennial logo and totem with the commemorative dates 1915-2015. The forearm’s right side bears the words THE ADMONITION which represents the core conviction that all Arrow men strive to attain. The Order of the Arrow has embodied brotherhood, cheerfulness, and service since its inception and Henry Repeating Arms is proud to recognize these fine men and thank them for their contributions to our country. Big Boy "Order of the Arrow Centennial Edition" Model Number H006OA Action Type Lever Action Caliber .44Mag/.44 Special Capacity 10 rounds Length 38 ½" Barrel Length 20" octagonal with 1:38rh rate of twist Weight 8.68 lbs. Stock Straight-grip American walnut Sights Adjustable Marble semi-buckhorn rear with white diamond insert and brass beaded front sight Finish Solid top brass receiver, brass buttplate and brass barrel band

title: For Sale:  Century Arms Centurion 39 AK47
postcontent:
Up for sale is an AK47 variant from Century International Arms. This is an AK built 100% here in America and even has an American flag on the side of the reciever. It is a milled reciever unlike normal stamped AKs, and it's milled from one block of 4140 steel. This AK is equipped with some unique features such as a windage adjustable rear sight like the one that is usually found on an RPK and can be adjusted with a hex wrench rather than a normal AK sight tool.  The rifle also features a Tapco G2 trigger that pulls at a predictable 4.5 pounds. It has laminated wooden furniture with the front handguard having a palm swell for a better grip.  It also has an aftermarket finger groove pistol instead of the standard peg grip.The bolt carrier has lightning cuts in it for fast cycling of the action. It has a 16" US made barrel and Up front is Century's proprietary chevron muzzle brake (14x1 LH) that does a good job of keeping the muzzle down on rapid fire. I am selling the rifle with the Tapco magazine it came with although it will accept any other brand AK mag As I have tried Magpul, surplus steel, Circle 10, US Palm, etc.  The rifle has a nice even parkerized finish.

I have about 400 rounds through the rifle with no problems. Shoots well and prints approx 2.5-3" MOA groups if you take your time since the trigger is nice which is standard for all AKs.  I'm selling the rifle in order to get some extra funds for the holiday. I am asking $600 OBO which is fair considering that what people try to charge for junk WASR AKs here on Armslist, and I can be reached at the reply email address or by texting me at 724seven146020.  Contact me if you would like anymore pictures.Thanks for viewing.
